      "writtenOn": "2026-05-27T14:57:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "```\nThe std::bad_function_call exception means connPolicy-\u003einvalidResp is an empty std::function.\n```\n\nThe cause is that ConnectionInfo object (this) is already destroyed when\nafterRead is called, leading to accessing correupted memory.\n```\n\nThis analysis doesn\u0027t seem correct.  If the std::function is empty, it shouldn\u0027t be null, it should be uncallable.  This is also tracking bind_front, not std::function.",
      "parentUuid": "5dba9668_401674bf",
      "revId": "0498b9d188bc1e4ef225e86162dbd4961f67e2cb",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
