      "writtenOn": "2026-05-27T20:47:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "both \"this\" and \"shared_from_this()\" are captured in the bind_front call.  This is a pattern we do a lot.  Because the shared_ptr is passed to the callback function, the shared_ptr MUST be valid at the time the callback is called (otherwise what would it call with?)\n\nThis is why I don\u0027t understand the statement that shared_from_this() Isn\u0027t captured.",
